Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. 10:09 AM; Case called for Plea hearing. Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Joshua Jontrell Staples in court.  Attorney Priya Barnes in court for Joshua Jontrell Staples.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer as listed in the document.  Atty. Barnes and the State confirm that offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 & 2, Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 & 2 (with the repeater enhancers struck).  Court orders Count 3 dismissed and read in. Court inquires if either party is requesting a PSI be prepared in this matter.  Neither the State nor Atty. Barnes are asking a PSI be prepared.  Atty. Barnes requests a sentencing date in December.  No objection by the State.  Court adjourns for sentencing.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 10:00 am.
**Reviewed by Judge Todd K. Martens on 09/22/22--Per court's oral decision.**
Plea hearing on September 26, 2022 at 09:30 am.

11:35 AM; Case called for Jury status hearing.   Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Joshua Jontrell Staples in court.  Attorney Priya Barnes in court for Joshua Jontrell Staples. Court notes the case is set for jury trial next week and inquires as to the status of the case.  Court also notes that the State has filed a motion to file an amended information and Defense filed a motion to withdraw as counsel.  Court will first address Defense's Motion to Withdraw.  Atty. Barnes outlines the reasons for the request to withdraw as counsel.  Court confirms with the defendant he plans to retain new counsel and inquires if the attorney is present today.  Defendant advises new counsel is not present today.  Atty. Barnes presents additional statements noting there has been a break-down in communication between her and her client.  Defendant responds, noting he has attempted to contact Atty. Barnes by telephone and email with no response from her.  For reasons placed on the record the Court will deny Atty. Barnes' Motion to Withdraw as counsel.  Court will maintain the previously scheduled jury trial set to begin on 09/27/2022, noting that if the defendant is able to retain new counsel the court will entertain a new request for adjournment at that time.  State is also asking the court address their motion to file an amended information.  Court will address the State's Motion to File an Amended Information.  Atty. Barnes objects to the motion.  Court raises concerns with the last minute filing of the amended information.  State presents statements in support of their motion.  Atty. Barnes presents additional statements.     State presents additional statements.  Court places its findings on the record.  For reasons placed on the record the Court will deny State's Motion to File an Amended Information.  Court notes the matter will remain set for jury trial next week starting at 8:30 on 9/27/2022. State recites the offer noting that as the matter is proceeding to trial next week it has been formally revoked.
Filed by Atty Barnes
Motion and Proposed Order to Withdraw as Counsel submitted by Atty. Barnes.
